    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "\n### Discussed in https://github.com/neovim/neovim/discussions/31300\n\n<div type='discussions-op-text'>\n\n<sup>Originally posted by **avidseeker** November 22, 2024</sup>\nIn Vim, `:set ft` returns the expected `markdown`\n```\n$ echo test | xz -c > test.md.xz && vim --clean test.md.xz\n```\nIn Neovim, `nvim --clean test.md.xz`, the `:set ft` is not set.\n\nThis seems to be a regression from #27931.\n\nIt seems that autocmd pattern matching actually matches with both the unexpanded filename and the expanded file name:\n```c\n  if (regmatch.regprog != NULL\n      && ((allow_dirs\n           && (vim_regexec(&regmatch, fname, 0)\n               || (sfname != NULL\n                   && vim_regexec(&regmatch, sfname, 0))))\n          || (!allow_dirs && vim_regexec(&regmatch, tail, 0)))) {\n    result = true;\n  }\n```\nThat'll be a bit complicated to replicate with `filetype.lua`...",
